{
  "texts": [
    "Unlike AI, human effort varies (Inzlicht et al., 2024; Perry, 2023).",
    "It's possible, therefore, that differences in performance between humans and LLMs are driven by reduced effort rather than skill.",
    "In the current project, we wish to answer this question by providing humans with differential incentives to improve their emotional support.",
    "Providing people EXPLORING HUMAN AND AI EMOTIONAL SUPPORT with differential incentives can also help shed light on a central debate in emotion regulation research: to what extent is emotion regulation driven by skill or by effort (Tamir et al., 2019).",
    "Not only may incentives reduce the gap between humans and GPT-4, but also the knowledge that the reappraisal was produced by AI."
  ]
}